reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My employees don't steal this brand.
reviews.reviewText: I've tried this myself. It get's the job done. It's not uncomfortable but it's also not what I'd want at home. Thankfully my employees feel the same way. Nobody's stolen any of it from the supply room. They take markers, pens and all the plastic silverware from the break room, but the toilet paper stays.Best for the price and a product that does what it supposed to with the added bones that most people wont want to steal it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What Toilet Paper Shortage?
reviews.reviewText: If these were normal times, I'd probably give this product about 4 stars, maybe even 3.5. But these aren't normal times. I've spent hours on Amazon, Instacart, the Wal-store website, etc. trying to find toilet paper, because I'm high-risk and am having everything delivered. I had reached the point where I was starting to stress about whether I'd be able to replace what I had before running out.Of the two brands of "normal" TP I've been able to buy during the quarantine but before the shortage got really bad, one of them is far inferior to this brand in every conceivable way - strength, texture, usefulness. The other is roughly equivalent to this one, probably slightly better, but one roll of this brand has almost as much TP as the entire package of 12 rolls of the other brand. And this one is a WAY better price for the quantity.And the best part is that not only will I not run out of TP this year, but I won't have to keep thinking about it and spending time trying to find some.In the world we're living in today, all of that is worth five of my stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have been buying this product for a year now. All the previous packages I have received have always been good. This last package I received, 2 of the rolls were damaged (pictures attached). The rolls are still useable, therefore I decided to keep it. It looked like the cutting machine got stuck or was not sharp enough when it cut, and they cut it again with another cutter. Besides that, it's still good. The toilet paper does its job. It's not Charming but it's good quality. It's soft enough where it does not hurt your bottom when you clean. I recommend it for a business.

reviews.reviewTitle: Soothing purchase that keeps on giving.
reviews.reviewText: Saved my ass. That's all I'm gonna say.Ok, in the interest of a legitimate quality review, it is not so thin as some describe and I even prefer it to the ultra thick cashmere-soft products. It is fine quality big-roll toilet paper that you might find at train stations, airports, etc. It will not rip unreasonably, and yes it does last a long time. I plan on using this after I am done with all twelve rolls, which will take me a long time, and yes I mean after the pandemic, too.It also sits nicely on my toilet paper holder (a stand-alone one) because though it is large, the core circumference is still small enough. And no I’m not getting paid to review this or anything, obviously.The hand in the roll is to show help give you an idea for the size. Twelve of these babies. Yes that is a lot.
Can you purchase a softer TP? Yes. Is this like using sandpaper? No. It removes the waste product with close to zero chance of a finger poking through.

I started buying these at the beginning of the COVID-19 pandemic in 2020 primarily because toilet paper was out of stock everywhere. First I thought it was pricey but all things considered, one order like this lasts me almost the entire year so I did end up saving quite a bit of money in the long run.
